  "texts": [
    "We will denote the ∞-category of 𝑑-homogeneous functors by Homog 𝑑 (Sp 𝜔, Sp).",
    "Since the ∞-category of 𝑑-excisive functors is closed under fibres, and a (𝑑 -1)-excisive functor is 𝑑-excisive, the 𝑑-th layer of the tower,𝐷 𝑑 𝐹 = fib(𝑃 𝑑 𝐹 -→ 𝑃 𝑑-1 𝐹), is 𝑑-homogeneous,and there is an adjunction 𝜄: Homog 𝑑 (Sp 𝜔, Sp) / / Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔, Sp): 𝐷 𝑑 o o, realising the ∞-category of 𝑑-homogeneous functors as a coreflexive sub-∞-category of the ∞-category of 𝑑-excisive functors.",
    "It follows that a 𝑑-excisive functor 𝐹 has a Goodwillie tower of the form 𝐹 𝑃 𝑑-1 𝐹 • • • 𝑃 1 𝐹 𝐷 𝑑 𝐹 𝐷 𝑑-1 𝐹 𝐷 1 𝐹.",
    "≃ The rational Goodwillie-Burnside ringOur attention now turns to the role of the abstract Burnside ring 𝐴 Q (𝑑) in Goodwillie calculus, a comprehensive account of which is given in [ABHS25, §8-9].",
    "We work rationally, as this allows us to simplify and streamline certain arguments, but integral versions of many of the statements in this section may be found in loc. cit.."
